User is not able to get error or alert message when text is entered instead of URL in the 'Skype' field.
column26:
DESCRIPTION:

The user is able to enter any text in the ‘Skype’ and no error/ alert message is displayed saying to specify only the URL.

STEPS TO REPRODUCE:

# Go to the homepage of the E-learning site
# Go to profile tab under ‘Home page’
# Go to personal data under the ‘Profile’ tab.
# Go to ‘Edit profile’ under the profile tab.
# Enter any text in the ‘Skype’ field.
# Click on the ‘save settings' button.

EXPECTED RESULT:

The user should be displayed with an error message saying “Please enter appropriate URL”.

ACTUAL RESULT:

The user is not getting any error or alert messages when no proper URL is entered in the ‘Skype' field.

IMAGE: inappropriate URL entered in the ‘Skype' field.

!image-20210907-121208.png|width=1182,height=130!

User is not able to get relevant error message when save settings button is clicked without entering password in the 'confirm password' field.
column26:
DESCRIPTION:

The user is not able to get a relevant error message when the ‘save settings’ button is clicked without entering any data in the ‘Confirm password’ field.

STEPS TO REPRODUCE:

# Go to the Homepage of the E-learning site
# Go to profile tab under home page section
# Go to the ‘Personal data’ section under the profile tab.
# Go to the Edit profile section under the profile tab.
# Enter the password in the ‘New password’ section
# Click on the ‘Save settings’ button without entering the password in the ‘Confirm password’ field.

EXPECTED RESULT:

User should get an error message saying, “Please enter the password in the ‘confirm password field”.

ACTUAL RESULT:

The user is able to get an error message saying, “You have typed two different passwords” while no password is entered in the ‘confirm password’ field.

!image-20210907-100016.png|width=742,height=262!

IMAGE: error message displayed when user failed to enter password in the ‘confirm password’ field.

column26:
DESCRIPTION:

The user is able to update the password without entering the current password in the ‘Pass’ field and no error or alert message is shown.



STEPS TO REPRODUCE:

# Go to Profile tab under home page tab
# Go to ‘Personal data’ under the ‘profile’ tab
# Go to ‘Edit profile’ under ‘Profile tab’ in the ‘Personal data’ section
# Go to ‘New password’ and enter a new password
# Go to the ‘Confirm password’ field and enter the new password again.
# Click on the ‘Save settings’ button without entering current password in the ‘Pass’ field.

EXPECTED RESULT:

The user should not be able to change the password without entering the current password in the ‘Pass’ field and the user should get an error or alert message.

ACTUAL RESULT:

The user is able to change a new password without entering the current password and no error or alert message is displayed.



!image-20210907-071258.png|width=798,height=574!

Image 1: User enters the new password in the ‘New password’ and ‘Confirm password’ fields and the ‘Pass’ field is kept empty.

!image-20210907-071023.png|width=1158,height=113!

image 2: The user is able to update the password without entering the current password in the ‘Pass’ field and a message is displayed for the same.

Go to the homepage in the E-learning site

Go to the profile tab under ‘Homepage’

Click on ‘Pending invitation’ from the ‘Profile’ tab.

Click on ‘Try and find some friends’ 

Click on the search button without entering any data in any fields

The User should be able to get an alert or error message when the search button is clicked without adding any data in any fields.



ACTUAL RESULT:

The User is not getting any alert or error message and no result is shown.
